## STEP 5 — VERIFY

Do not commit until verified. Run in this order:

```bash
# 1. Type check — no TypeScript errors
npx tsc --noEmit

# 2. Lint — clean
npx eslint src/ --ext .ts,.tsx --max-warnings 0

# 3. Tests — nothing broken
npx vitest run
# or
npx jest --passWithNoTests

# 4. Build — confirm it compiles for production
npx vite build
# or
npx next build

# 5. Spot check — if the fix touches a visible component, open it in browser and verify:
#    - Loading state appears while fetching
#    - Error state appears if the request fails (use network throttle or mock)
#    - Empty state appears with no data
#    - No console errors or warnings in browser devtools
```

If tests fail:
- Pre-existing and unrelated to your change → note in commit, proceed
- Caused by your change → fix before committing

---

## STEP 6 — COMMIT

One commit per fix. Never batch.

### Commit message format:

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>

<body — what was wrong, what was fixed, why it matters>

Gap: <category — e.g. "State Management / Category B">
Risk: <what breaks in production without this>
Files: <list of changed files>
```

### Types:
- `fix` — correcting a bug or broken pattern
- `obs` — observability (error boundaries, logging, error tracking)
- `perf` — performance (memoization, code splitting, virtualization)
- `state` — state management improvement
- `arch` — component architecture (extraction, decomposition, co-location)
- `types` — type safety improvement
- `api` — API integration pattern
- `chore` — dead code, constants, organization

### Example:

```
state(tasks): replace useState fetch with React Query in TaskList

TaskList.tsx was fetching tasks with useState/useEffect in 3 separate
components. Each maintained its own loading state with no cache sharing.
After mutations, views showed stale data until remount.

Extracted to useTasksQuery hook with React Query. All 3 components now
share the cache. Added invalidation on task create/update/delete.
Added loading skeleton, error state, and empty state to each call site.

Gap: State Management / Category B
Risk: Stale data after mutations, inconsistent loading states across views
Files: hooks/useTasksQuery.ts, components/TaskList.tsx, components/TaskSidebar.tsx, components/TaskDashboard.tsx
```

```bash
git add -p
git commit -m "..."
git push origin HEAD
```

---

## STEP 7 — STOP

You are done. Output one line:

```
Done: [what you fixed] in [file(s)]. Committed as [type(scope): description].
```

The next run picks up the next highest-value gap.

